   "body" : "Hi there!\r\nWe are trying to run full-node on AWS EC2 r5.large instance with 16GB RAM but we are facing a strange issue. Despite any options listed here bitcoind memory usage constantly grows, so ~6min after start it uses 100% of RAM.\r\n\r\nHere is the command we use to run bitcoind:\r\n```\r\nusr/local/bin/bitcoind -daemon \\\r\n-pid=/run/bitcoind/bitcoind.pid \\\r\n-conf=/etc/bitcoin/bitcoin.conf \\\r\n-datadir=/data/bitcoind \\\r\n-txindex=1 \\\r\n-sysperms=true \\\r\n-dbcache=5000 \\\r\n-maxmempool=100\r\n```\r\nHow can we limit bitcoind memory usage? Thanks in advance",
